  PhD position in glycobioinformatics

*Start date
* 	*Application deadline*
01.11.2013 	31.07.2013
*Employment fraction* 	*Job reference *
Full-time 	PhD position in glycobioinformatics
*City* 	*Type of contract*
Geneva 	Temporary
*Employer* 	
SIB Swiss Institute of Bioinformatics 	


*Job description

*

The PhD position is attached to an EU-Marie Curie International Training 
Network 
<http://ec.europa.eu/euraxess/index.cfm/jobs/jobDetails/33861562> 
devoted to the study of gastric cancer with glycomic technology. A whole 
range of experimental data will be produced from patient samples and 
will involve molecular and cellular screens assessing the role of 
glycans. The glycobioinformatics PhD position focuses on method 
development for standardizing, collecting and integrating the data obtained.

*Job tasks

*

  * understanding the different types of data generated within the project
  * defining data formats for data collection in agreement with data
    producers
  * designing a pipeline for collecting the data
  * connecting the new data to existing glycoinformatics resources
  * developing intelligent search tools for exploring the data


*Profile requirements

*

Successful applicants are expected to have a masters degree in 
bioinformatics or computer science with skills in Java programming.
Knowledge of mass spectrometry and basics in glycobiology is a definite 
advantage.

*Please send your application to

*Please follow the application guidelines concerning Early Stage 
Researcher (PhD positions) and Experienced Researcher Fellowships 
(postdoctoral positions) in the Marie Curie Initial Training Network 
"GastricGlycoExpoler -- Systems Glycobiology of Gastric Cancer".

http://ec.europa.eu/euraxess/index.cfm/jobs/jobDetails/33861562

When an application fulfilling the requirements is received, then a 
message is sent out to the applicant acknowledging that it will be 
reviewed.*
*

